1. d4 e6 {1...Nf6 and 1...d5 are more common but the text move is a subtle move-order change avoiding lines of the Trompowsky attack after 1.d4 Nf6 2.Bg5}
2.c4 Nf6 

3.Nf3 {Avoiding the Nimzo-Indian}

3...Bb4+ {The Bogo-Indian defence}

4.Nbd2 {A passive option that aims to win retain the Bishop pair}

4...b6 {Black will fianchetto the other Bishop}

5.a3 {White wants the Bishop pair}

5...Bxd2+ {Black gives up the Bishop pair}

6.Qxd2 {A passive move blocking the dark-squared Bishop.6.Bxd2 is the better move}

6...Bb7 {Controlling the a8-h1 diagonal}

7.e3 {White wants to develop his Kingside now}

7...O-O {Black completes the Kingside development and also brings the Rook into the game} 

8.Be2 {White too intends to O-O soon}

8...a5 {White wants to O-O and play b4 gaining space on the Queenside. White will then follow up with Bb2.This move prevents White 
from pushing b2-b4}

9.b3 {White does not allow Black to push ...a4 which would make the pawn push b2-b3 impossible and throttle his Queenside development}

9...d6 {Prepares ...Nbd7 followed by the pawn push ...e5 or ...c5}

10.Bb2 {A natural follow-up to the last move where the dark-squared Bishop is fianchettoed}

10...Ne4!? {Black occupies the e4 square with a tempo on the White Queen. Black plans to play ...Nbd7,...f5 and a possible ...c5 or ...e5.}

11.Qc2 {The Queen now eyes the Knight and White threatens to cut off the Bishop-Knight combination on e4 with the pawn push d5}

11...Nd7 {More control over the c5 and e5 squares}

12.O-O {White completes his development and connects the Rooks}

12...f5 {Black overprotects the e4 square as White threatens to push d5 soon}

13.d5 {White gains space in the centre and creates a light-square pawn complex on the Queenside squares b3-c4-d5. I feel that this pawn advance is a little premature where White commits his pawn structure.
13.Rad1 looks more flexible where White threatens d5 later.}

13...e5 {Keeping the centre closed and gaining space.Black is now ready to play on the Kingside with moves like ...Rf6,...Rg6 or even ...Ng5}

14.Nd2* {White wants the pesky Knight on e4 to be traded. White also prepares to push f3-f4 or f4 to gain space and make his pieces active}


